      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;telescope-setup&#34; class=&#34;mt-8 mb-3 text-xl sm:text-2xl text-white&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;relative inline-block&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;      Telescope setup&#xD;&#xA;      &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute left-0 -bottom-1 h-px w-0 bg-indigo-400&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&#34;mx-auto my-6 rounded-md border border-gray-800/70 bg-black/20&#34; src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/images/telescope.png&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xD;&#xA;  alt=&#34;telescope&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;camera&#34; class=&#34;mt-8 mb-3 text-xl sm:text-2xl text-white&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;relative inline-block&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;      Camera&#xD;&#xA;      &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute left-0 -bottom-1 h-px w-0 bg-indigo-400&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Nikon D3500 - full spectrum modified.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you are curious to mod your own, I&amp;rsquo;ve made a tutorial for it because at the time I did not have a tutorial to follow for this camera model.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As you can tell by the picture my camera also has an old PC fan and small heat sink attached to it, to keep the sensor cooler while doing long exposures.xd&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>File upload to XSS</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/xss_file_upload/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 18:03:42 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/xss_file_upload/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;validating-and-exploiting-cdn-subdomain-xss&#34; class=&#34; mt-8 mb-3 text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-white&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;relative inline-block&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;      Validating and exploiting CDN subdomain XSS&#xD;&#xA;      &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute left-0 -bottom-1 h-px w-0 bg-indigo-400&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;How can unrestricted file upload to CDN lead to XSS vulenerability with impact?&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Requirements:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Endpoint that allows the user to upload and access HTML file.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;SameSite cookie flag is set as &lt;strong&gt;Lax&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;None&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;CDN is a trusted origin for requests to target subdomains.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Bonus - important cookies are not &lt;strong&gt;HttpOnly&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;uploading-html-file&#34; class=&#34;mt-8 mb-3 text-xl sm:text-2xl text-white&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;relative inline-block&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;      Uploading HTML file&#xD;&#xA;      &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute left-0 -bottom-1 h-px w-0 bg-indigo-400&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Capture the file upload request in your proxy, and modify it&amp;rsquo;s content with benign html.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Intigriti ctf 0526</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/intigriti_ctf_0526/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 17:20:57 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/intigriti_ctf_0526/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;task&#34; class=&#34;mt-8 mb-3 text-xl sm:text-2xl text-white&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;relative inline-block&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;      Task&#xD;&#xA;      &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute left-0 -bottom-1 h-px w-0 bg-indigo-400&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Leverage XSS vulnerability on the challenge page.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Should not be self XSS or related MITM attacks.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;initial-observations&#34; class=&#34;mt-8 mb-3 text-xl sm:text-2xl text-white&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;relative inline-block&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;      Initial observations&#xD;&#xA;      &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute left-0 -bottom-1 h-px w-0 bg-indigo-400&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;After making a user account and walking the application I found couple POST endpoints which store user input and render it in other places.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;/api/register&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;/api/login&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;/api/testimonials&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;/api/profile&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Also, the session cookie was not HttpOnly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
